---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="BYOC Deployment Terms - AnswerLayer"
  description="AnswerLayer terms that apply to customer-hosted Bring Your Own Cloud deployments."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container legal-content">
      <h1>BYOC Deployment Terms</h1>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Last updated: March 31, 2026</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-8">
        These terms supplement the <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> and apply only if you create,
        manage, or use a Bring Your Own Cloud deployment of AnswerLayer.
      </p>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">1. Scope</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          A Bring Your Own Cloud, or BYOC, deployment means an AnswerLayer deployment launched into
          infrastructure controlled by you or your cloud provider account rather than solely hosted by
          AnswerLayer.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          These BYOC Deployment Terms apply in addition to the Terms of Service. If there is a
          conflict between these BYOC Deployment Terms and the Terms of Service, these BYOC Deployment
          Terms control for BYOC deployments.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">2. Your Cloud Environment</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You are responsible for your cloud account, VPCs, networking, DNS, certificates, IAM,
          logging, security controls, infrastructure costs, and any other resources used in
          connection with your BYOC deployment.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You are also responsible for the accuracy of the deployment information you provide,
          including AWS account identifiers, regions, domain configuration, and certificate details.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          AnswerLayer is not responsible for failures, delays, outages, security events, or data
          exposure caused by your cloud environment, your configuration choices, your cloud provider,
          or third-party infrastructure under your control.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">3. Deployment and Operation</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          BYOC deployment workflows may provision or configure infrastructure in your environment
          using third-party deployment tooling, cloud provider workflows, and CloudFormation or
          similar templates.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You are responsible for reviewing deployment parameters before launch and for determining
          whether the resulting environment is appropriate for your security, operational, legal, and
          compliance requirements.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          AnswerLayer may modify supported deployment patterns, required inputs, or supported cloud
          regions over time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">4. Cloud Charges and Third-Party Terms</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You are solely responsible for all charges from AWS and any other third-party providers used
          in connection with a BYOC deployment, including compute, storage, networking, load
          balancers, certificates, data transfer, logging, and related services.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Your use of AWS and any other third-party products or services is governed by the terms you
          have with those providers. AnswerLayer is not responsible for third-party service
          availability, changes, pricing, or deprecations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">5. Security and Shared Responsibility</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          AnswerLayer is responsible only for the portions of the BYOC deployment workflow and
          software that AnswerLayer expressly agrees to provide. You remain responsible for your
          broader cloud security posture, access controls, secrets management, network boundaries,
          compliance obligations, backups, and business continuity planning.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You should validate the security and correctness of your deployed environment before
          production use, including by testing networking, certificates, monitoring, and access
          policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">6. Data Handling in BYOC</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          In a BYOC deployment, Customer Data may be processed within infrastructure that you control,
          but AnswerLayer and its subprocessors may still process deployment metadata, support data,
          logs, diagnostics, and service-related information as needed to provide the platform,
          support the deployment, and improve the Service, subject to the Terms of Service and
          applicable law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">7. Deletion and Deprovisioning</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          If you delete or tear down a BYOC deployment through AnswerLayer or its deployment tooling,
          that action may trigger deprovisioning of infrastructure, applications, or related resources
          in your cloud environment.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You are responsible for understanding the operational effect of deletion actions before you
          take them. Deletion may result in downtime, loss of access, removal of deployed components,
          or other irreversible effects.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">8. Support and Service Levels</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Unless AnswerLayer expressly agrees otherwise in an order form, statement of work, or other
          written agreement, BYOC deployments are provided without a separate service level agreement
          and without any obligation to provide custom infrastructure operations, incident response, or
          environment-specific remediation beyond standard product support.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">9. Termination</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Termination of your account, subscription, or BYOC deployment does not by itself eliminate
          obligations you may have to your cloud provider or other third parties. You remain
          responsible for any ongoing cloud resources and charges unless and until those resources are
          properly deprovisioned.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4">10. Enterprise Agreements Control</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          If you and AnswerLayer have entered into a separate master services agreement, order form,
          statement of work, or other written agreement covering BYOC deployments, that agreement will
          control to the extent it conflicts with these BYOC Deployment Terms.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
